      <ul class="progressbar">
        <li class="active">Explore</li>
        <li class="active">Project</li>
        <li>Image</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="container"><br>
      <h1>Anime Girls</h1>
      <p class="by-line">by Jane Lim</p>
      <p>I am trying to create more anime art so here is my project</p>
      <!--
      Note: Overall structure for the code was taken from free, open-source websites. The code is NOT an exact copy of the open-source code, as adaptions were made regarding the implementation, but a large percentage of our code remains identical to the source.

      Code for this timeline was taken from https://codepen.io/melnik909/pen/qPjwvq, from the website, http://freefrontend.com/css-timelines/#horizontal-timelines, which lists many different types of frontends. This code has been adjusted to fit in with our website, but by and large it remains the same.

      A tutorial on how to implement and create a timeline was also followed in the creation of this code: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eEybqzuh6Z0. While they use different timelines, the final implementation takes aspects from both.
     -->

      <div class="page">
        <div class="page__demo">
          <div class="main-container page__container">
            <div class="timeline">
              <div class="timeline__group">
                <span class="timeline__year">2008</span>
                <div class="timeline__box">
                  <div class="timeline__date">
                    <span class="timeline__day">2</span>
                    <span class="timeline__month">Feb</span>
                  </div>
                  <div class="timeline__post">
                    <div class="timeline__content">
                      <p>I didn't really know what I wanted to draw, but then I took some inspiration from this anime I was watching and sketched out this girl. No idea what I'm going to do next :')</p>
                      <div class="dropdown-divider"></div>
                      <div class="timeline-image image1" onclick="window.location='/users/5/5/5';"></div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline__box">
                  <div class="timeline__date">
                    <span class="timeline__day">12</span>
                    <span class="timeline__month">Feb</span>
                  </div>
                  <div class="timeline__post">
                    <div class="timeline__content">
                      <p>Feeling sooo lazy this week, and I'm totally swamped by exams so I didn't really draw this past week... But I have a good idea of what I'll add next week!</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="timeline__group">
                <div class="timeline__box">
                  <div class="timeline__date">
                    <span class="timeline__day">21</span>
                    <span class="timeline__month">Feb</span>
                  </div>
                  <div class="timeline__post">
                    <div class="timeline__content">
                      <p>Ta dah! I think the bird really adds a nice touch :)</p>
                      <div class="dropdown-divider"></div>
                      <div class="timeline-image image2" onclick="window.location='/users/5/5/5';"></div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="timeline__group">
                <span class="timeline__year">2009</span>
                <div class="timeline__box">
                  <div class="timeline__date">
                    <span class="timeline__day">28</span>
                    <span class="timeline__month">Aug</span>
                  </div>
                  <div class="timeline__post">
                    <div class="timeline__content">
                      <p>Wow it's been almost a year since I touched this project! I ended up drawing a bunch of other things before getting back to this one - I was rly happy with it. </br> But when I was going through my pictures again, I really thought that a background would be nice... so here ya go!</p>
                      <div class="dropdown-divider"></div>
                      <div class="timeline-image image3" onclick="window.location='/users/5/5/5';"></div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <footer>
        <div class="additional__note">
          <p>Note: Code was adapted and built from open-sourced software. You can find additional timelines like this from <a href="http://freefrontend.com/css-timelines/#horizontal-timelines">here</a> and the timeline we originally used <a href="https://codepen.io/melnik909/pen/qPjwvq">here</a></p>
        </div>
        <p>Copyright &copy; 2018</p>
      </footer>
    </div>
